Dr. Barry Spatz<br>
I promised you a response to your postings on site.  To tell you the truth, I have no idea how.  In one(or two) fell swoop, you have given me what I have been asking, pleading, begging for, and more, since I have been on site.  My response to you and your writings would not do you or them justice.  All night long, I have been trying to assimilate all that you have given me, but sometimes I am my own worst enemy.  A flood of memories of past events, past traumas, combat and non-combat related have been getting in the way. It will take me more than twenty four hours.<br><br>
&gt;By the way, Doc Del, I was the one who did 2 years of bed pans instead of running to Canada-your comment that I lost<br>
my credibility was curious-perhaps you might enlighten me as to how that happened or why you think so.&lt;<br><br>
&gt;I used to think, and my first posting on this site, said that I was tired of viet nam vets and their &quot;whinning&quot;&lt;<br><br>
I HAVE read All the postings from beginning to current, many, many times.  I have tried to overlook those things written that I have considered personally offensive or hurtful trying to see beyond them so I could extract what I needed.  In this respect, I have failed.  Your very first posting/attack stuck with me, no matter how hard I tried to shake it.  Your subsequent postings, the yelling and screaming and bantering tired me, wore me down.  They discouraged me.<br><br>
If what I wrote about your credibility, contributed to your latest postings, I am not sorry.  If it did not have anything to do with you coming back on site, I am indeed grateful that you were able to look past my own prejudices and still give me what you have.  In any case, it seems that what I wrote was wrong.  You have my deepest apology.
